
[1]white

   WHITE, a. [G.]

   1. Being in the color of pure snow; snowy; not dark; as white paper; a
   white skin.

   2. Pale; destitute of color in the cheeks, or of the tinge of blood
   color; as white with fear.

   3. Having the color of purity; pure; clean; free from spot; as white
   robed innocence.

   4. Gray; as white hair; a venerable man, white with age.

   5. Pure; unblemished.

   No whiter page than Addisons remains.

   6. In a scriptural sense, purified from sin; sanctified. Psalm 51.
